<!--112-->Morgul Gates x 4     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">it&#39;s the Fun version of my deck &quot;Aragorn and his court counter the malicious nazguls v2&quot;<br />
<br />
There is 8 compagions => a lot for enquea and greed, and 5 compagions culture => a lot for the new grima<br />
<br />
<B>BUT IT&#39;S A FUN DECK NOT A COMPETITIVE ONE</B><br />
<br />
Fellowship strategy <br />
<br />
Aragorn Heal each turn one compagion. (except eomer )<br />
<br />
<B>For winning skirmish </B><br />
-Help in Doubt and Need Eowyn/Eomer/Aragorn/Boromir (After heal with Hard Choice) <br />
-Servant of secret fire<br />
-No mere ranger<br />
<br />
<B>For Archery </B><br />
Against Dunland : Use the Aragorn&#39;s Bow to kill them at the archery (Hides is a shimmer cards because it&#39;s horrible to play against) <br />
<br />
<B>For Condition </B><br />
Use Sleep to discard them <br />
<br />
<B>For Burdenssssss </B><br />
Use Sam to remove them and kill him to slim your fellowship ( you play a big fellowship ) <br />
<br />
Don&#39;t worry your compagion take a lot of wounds but a lot, but they survive !<br />
<br />
Shadow Strategy <br />
<br />
Play Big nazgul to stop your opponent <br />
<br />
The 4 first sites are Plains so use your black steed. <br />
<br />
If you are lucky the site 2 Wold of rohan is THE site to play attea with a black steed ( beacause at each assgnement the opponent add 1 in the twilight, so you can raise the strength of Attea) <br />
<br />
Play some blade tip is very fun,<br />
<br />
<B>Very Important</B>If you play against a frodo with the Answer to All Riddles ring : <br />
-Play a nazgul ( a big one)<br />
-Play bill ferny<br />
-Assign bill ferny to frodo and if he put the one ring to get strength + 2 play <B>Return to its master</B><br />
<br />
Have a nice play<br />
<br />
<B>Remember before playing, take a lot of red wound token</B><br />
<br />
